57:07.560 --> 57:13.880
So again, this kind of collaboration is absolutely critical if we're going to reflect that rationale

57:13.880 --> 57:17.640
of best practices when it comes to open source, but also best practice in terms of the tools

57:17.640 --> 57:20.760
that we're talking about into the law, into the practice.

57:20.760 --> 57:26.920
Otherwise, there will be unintended consequences, and I think nobody wants to hear that.

57:26.920 --> 57:34.040
I think the final point I want to make just before I hand over to our first panelist is

57:34.040 --> 57:40.440
that even if we get the open source exclusion and some of the clarity into the text and

57:40.440 --> 57:46.880
the articles around open source, it's still kind of half of the journey.

57:46.880 --> 57:49.120
And I think that's important just to underscore.

57:49.120 --> 57:55.460
There are still elements which need further discussion, how they practically impact this

57:55.460 --> 57:59.640
extraordinary ecosystem.

