obviously if we have someone that comes for the open source community that says that he's

01:35:52.400 --> 01:35:56.560
speaking for the community, then he would bind everyone.

01:35:56.560 --> 01:36:02.600
So you know, those companies that have those trade associations, et cetera, this also gives

01:36:02.600 --> 01:36:08.040
a framework for us to really say, okay, this is a voice of this sector, this sector, this

01:36:08.040 --> 01:36:09.040
sector.

01:36:09.040 --> 01:36:13.360
If we do not have this, it's a bit complicated for us to take it as just being the voice

01:36:13.360 --> 01:36:19.040
of the entire community, because you can have an opinion and someone else can have another

01:36:19.040 --> 01:36:23.560
one, but then which one do I have to consider as being the one of this community?

01:36:23.560 --> 01:36:28.040
That's a bit of the complexity also for us, just to be honest.

